# {{mathematics}} An element of a [[completion]] of the field of [[rational number]]s which has a [[p-adic ultrametric|''p''-adic ultrametric]] as its [[metric]].<ref>'''2008''', Jacqui Ramagge, [http://www.uow.edu.au/content/groups/public/@web/@inf/@math/documents/web/uow061321.pdf Unreal numbers: The story of ''p''-adic numbers]</ref>
#: The expansion (21)2121<sub>''p''</sub> is equal to the rational <b>''p''-adic number</b> <math>{2 p + 1 \over p^2 - 1}</math>.

====Usage notes====
* The '<i>p</i>' in "''p''-adic" is a parameter which stands for a positive integer, preferably a [[prime number]].
* For a fixed prime value of ''p'', a <b>''p''-adic number</b> is a member of the [[field]] <math>\mathbb{Q}_p</math> which is a completion of the set of rational numbers.
* For a composite value of ''p'', a <b>''p''-adic number</b> is a member of a ring which is an extension of the field of rational numbers. <!-- Is it also a completion? --> 

